✨Overjoyed to announce I’m carrying our little angel baby ✨ ⁣⁣
⁣⁣
I’ve been slower to respond, quieter on here than usual, having to say “no” more than I ever have before, but gosh I am just OVER THE MOON and soaking up every second of this special time I’ve dreamt of for so so long.⁣⁣
⁣⁣
All I’ve ever wanted to be was a mom! It’s been a journey -but- I just want to thank each of my clients and photographer friends (you know who you are) that have prayed for me and my husband, held my emotional hand and checked on me repeatedly!! The ones who have given me so much grace, and forgiven me for not being able to be at their wedding days. Who have cheered for us continuously and are celebrating this incredible news with us! Thank you for loving me and making me feel so supported!! 🥹 ⁣your friendship and kindness mean more than you guys could ever know! 
⁣
Photos by @7sistersphotography

FAMILIES FAMILIES FAMILIES 🍂 Fall family sessions - Christmas card pics! Let’s get you in the books!! ⁣
⁣
I’m going to be shooting both full sessions and adding a few mini sessions on Sundays in November! ⁣
⁣
Full sessions include at least 75+ images which can be awesome if you have active kiddos as this gives you plenty of pictures to choose from! I have several weekday evenings to choose from in November! ⁣
⁣
My mini sessions are going to be 30 images and 20 mins of shoot time together. If you’re interested in securing a mini please reach out via email or Instagram message, or if you’re an existing client text me 🤎⁣
⁣
No these are not just for families! If you are a senior or couple you can also book. All minis will be shot at one location. ⁣
⁣
The Bell’s family session was a full! We did several location changes on the ranch and an outfit change. We usually shoot for an hour to an hour and a half together! ⁣
⁣

Me & my little girlie made it through October !! ⁣
⁣
3 weddings & a few special shoots to kick off me jumping back into work.⁣
⁣
I was terrified, and some of my fears came true (aka she refused a bottle while I was working a wedding and I felt like an awful mother) BUT all in all we survived and we did it!! I’m so proud of myself both mentally and physically because I know I’m exhausted but I’m still pushing through and just figuring this out as I go. ⁣
⁣
⁣
reminding myself daily when I question if I should keep pursuing this - that this was the dream! Running my own business and getting to be with my little one is the dream. ⁣
But gosh dang it is hardddd… I’m constantly doubting if I’m doing it well enough and if things will get easier with her (LAUGH OUT LOUD right?) ⁣
⁣
My books are currently closed for the rest of Fall season. We’ll be doing lots of cuddling & lots of editing during the holiday season as I get into a rhythm! ⁣
⁣
2024 Wedding Books are currently still open - not sure how many more I will be taking on but until I decide that they are still open 😅🥰 ⁣
⁣
THANK YOU THANK YOU THANK YOU for supporting me through all these years and seasons. For making this dream a reality!! If you’re a one time client or I get to shoot with you guys every year- you’re so appreciated and loved by me!! 🥹
